## Types:
# 0: Core repository, the highest priority in downloading
# 1: Local repositories
# 2: Extra repositories, still has the same priority as the Core
# 3: Community repositories, if something happens, it will not be downloaded

## For other people repositories, use Level 2
## For helpers for other building platforms and they need a local copy, use Level 1
## For other extra repositories that doesn't need a lot of power, Level 3

repo core
server http://lkmnds.github.com/yapi/database/core
type 0
end

repo extra
server http://lkmnds.github.com/yapi/database/extra
type 2
end

repo community
server http://lkmnds.github.com/yapi/database/community
type 3
end

## Other users repositories
#repo user
#server http://their.server/database/user
#end

## Custom repository
#repo custom
#file /home/packages/custom-db
#type 1
#end

## Special repository, only for tests, and only that.
#repo bomb
#file /home/packages/tests-db
#type 4 ; this makes the magic happen(all files will be marked to be run in containers)
#end
